import * as React from 'react';
import { View} from 'react-native';
import { Button } from 'react-native-web';
import {  Header,
          Container,
          HeaderButtonLeft,
          HeaderButtonRight,
          Container1,
          Tex1,
          Text2,
          Container2,
          Text3,
          Text4,
          Container3,
          Container4,
          Container5,
          Container6
        } 
from './styles';
import { Entypo } from '@expo/vector-icons';
import { Ionicons } from '@expo/vector-icons';


function MealScheduleScreen({navigation,route}) {
  const item = route.params;
  return (
    <Container>
      <Header>
        <HeaderButtonLeft>
          <Ionicons name="chevron-back" size={20} color={"black"} onPress={navigation.goBack} />
        </HeaderButtonLeft>
        <HeaderButtonRight>
          <Entypo name="dots-two-horizontal" size={20} color="black" />
        </HeaderButtonRight>
        </Header>
        <Container1></Container1>
        <Tex1>Fri</Tex1>
        <Text2>14</Text2>
        <Container2></Container2>
        <Text3>Fri</Text3>
        <Text4>14</Text4>
        <Container3></Container3>
        <Tex5>Fri</Tex5>
        <Text6>14</Text6>
        <Container4></Container4>
        <Tex7>Fri</Tex7>
        <Text8>14</Text8>
        <Container5></Container5>
        <Tex9>Fri</Tex9>
        <Text10>14</Text10>
        <Container6></Container6>
        <Tex11>Fri</Tex11>
        <Text12>14</Text12>
        <Button
          title="Go to Add Alarm "
          onPress={() => navigation.navigate('Add Alarm')}
        /> 
    </Container>
  );
}
export default MealScheduleScreen;
